The paper proposes a reinforcement learning model for scheduling workloads onto heterogeneous processors, which falls under the domain of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The focus is on scheduling in datacenters, which suggests a sub-category of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). The paper also mentions the use of domain knowledge to reduce training data and time, which is a common theme in machine learning (cs.LG). The scheduling problem involves making decisions in a dynamic environment, which can be modeled as a control problem, falling under the sub-category of control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper proposes a new approach to scheduling, which can be considered a contribution to programming languages and compilers (cs.PL).
